{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"l6kravc26pl7ixjyg5o3nlk","title":"Arrays","desc":"","updated":1713644093667,"created":1712949538100,"custom":{},"fname":"lang.java.lib.arrays","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"518f658b8e24d679d712cb1f527de6df","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.arrays","id":"l6kravc26pl7ixjyg5o3nlk","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.serializable","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":31,"offset":892},"end":{"line":31,"column":79,"offset":940},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.serializable"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.arrays","id":"l6kravc26pl7ixjyg5o3nlk","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.cloneable","position":{"start":{"line":31,"column":85,"offset":946},"end":{"line":31,"column":130,"offset":991},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.interfaces.marker.cloneable"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.lib.arrays","id":"l6kravc26pl7ixjyg5o3nlk","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"type theory.casting.object.upcasting","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":56,"offset":1049},"end":{"line":32,"column":96,"offset":1089},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"type theory.casting.object.upcasting"}}],"anchors":{"arrays-in-java-are-objects":{"type":"header","text":"Arrays in Java are Objects","value":"arrays-in-java-are-objects","line":9,"column":0,"depth":2},"corresponding-class-names-for-some-array-types":{"type":"header","text":"Corresponding class names for some array types","value":"corresponding-class-names-for-some-array-types","line":22,"column":0,"depth":3},"references":{"type":"header","text":"References","value":"references","line":41,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"9zir47v5yk3jbddsjyqkt53","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"arrays\">Arrays<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#arrays\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"arrays-in-java-are-objects\">Arrays in Java are Objects<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#arrays-in-java-are-objects\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>This is why arrays are initialized using <code>new</code> keyword</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>For each array type, there exists a corresponding class.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>So there is a class for int[], for float[], double[] etc.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>These classes are the part of java language and not available to the programmer level</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>To know the class of any array</p>\n<pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Here x is the name of the array.</span>\n<span class=\"token class-name\">System</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>out<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>x<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getClass</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getName</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"corresponding-class-names-for-some-array-types\">Corresponding class names for some array types<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#corresponding-class-names-for-some-array-types\"></a></h3>\n<pre class=\"language-plain\"><code class=\"language-plain\">Array typeCorresponding          Class Name\nint[]                            [I\nint[][]                          [[I\ndouble[]                         [D\ndouble[][]                       [[D\nshort[]                          [S\nbyte[]                           [B\nboolean[]                        [Z\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p>[ for single dimension\n[[ for two-dimensional</p>\n</blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>Every array type implements <a href=\"/cs/notes/mbwwjk3x17fjagziw7d0ky6\">Serializable</a>  and <a href=\"/cs/notes/6fe2bcmqj3rdsd3wd82k3lp\">Cloneable</a>. </li>\n<li>Arrays can be assigned to variables of type Object — <a href=\"/cs/notes/0wsnptopg4m3w3wp2qtjngv\">Upcasting</a>.</li>\n<li>All methods of Object class can be invoked on an array</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"references\">References<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#references\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/array-primitive-type-object-java/\">Is an array a primitive type or an object in Java? - GeeksforGeeks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se7/html/jls-10.html\">Chapter 10. Arrays - Oracle Docs</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","title":"Computer Science","desc":"","updated":1715103618849,"created":1713296516553,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"36faf26c6be438d4aed355d72b55a110","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"arch","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":3,"offset":105},"end":{"line":6,"column":11,"offset":113},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"arch"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"paradigm","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":3,"offset":159},"end":{"line":11,"column":15,"offset":171},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"paradigm"}}],"anchors":{"references":{"type":"header","text":"References","value":"references","line":23,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["0xgibr34qhbv1edksyoxakk","t246wcci6dy9lnof7l1os4l","71sipcgr0pdqyxnmntvx28w","6k8qk8m6zofpfla0wr8eajn